# Attack Vectors

## What I Learned
Today I reviewed different types of human and system attack vectors.

## Common Human Attack Vectors
  Social engineering, which is the exploitation of human error that threat actors use to gain access to systems or accounts. 
  examples of social engineering are:

- Phishing Emails (the most common type)
- Impersonation 

## Common System Attack Vectors
- Human led attacks such as malicious usbs, downloading malware, or reusing passwords.
- Vulnerablilities within software. 
- Supply chain attacks.

## Ways to mitigate both human and system attack vectors
There are many ways to help mitigate both human and system attack vectors such as:
- antivirus (human)
- system awareness training for employees (human)
- patches (systems)
- EDR (systems)

## Reflection
I learned that within technology, you don't just have to worry about system vulnerabilities, you also have to worry about human error
as humans are often seen as the "weakest link" in cybersecurity threats.
